Description. Adult ( Figs 10, 11 )—Forewing length 13–16 mm in males (n= 171);
13 – 16 mm
in females (n= 61). Antenna filiform in male, ciliate in female. Head and thorax covered with brown scales. Forewing ground color brown fringed with ochreous scales. Forewing antemedial line wave-like, postmedial line serrate; orbicular stigma round, reniform stigma wide bean-like, both surrounding with pale ochreous; submarginal line pale ochreous, rather straight; outer margin with small triangular dot locating at central part between each vein; marginal line pale ochreous; cilia brown. Hindwing slight paler than forewing, discal spot indistinct but traceable, marginal line pale ochreous, cilia brown. Abdomen brown.

Female genitalia (
Fig. 27
)—Ovipositor elongated, papillae anales weak. Posterior apophyses thin, 1.5X length of anterior ones. Antrum wide, flat. Ductus bursae wide, flat, strongly sclerotized with ¼ section from posterior part bent. Bursae copulatrix sclerotized except apical part where ductus seminalis arising. Corpus bursae slightly granular with rigtht side sclerotized, without signum.
